{"cursor":"4784","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"{{Infobox Anatomy | Name = Mesentery | Latin = Mesenterium| GraySubject = 246 |\nGrayPage = 1157 | Image = Gray1038.png | Caption = Horizontal disposition of the\nperitoneum in the lower part of the abdomen. The mesentery is marked with red.|\nImage2 = Gray1035.png | Caption2 = Vertical disposition of the peritoneum. Main\ncavity, red; omental bursa, blue. | Width = 300 | System = | MeshName =\nMesentery | MeshNumber = A01.047.025.600.451 | }} In anatomy, the 'mesentery' is\nthe double layer of peritoneum that suspends the jejunum and ileum from the\nposterior wall of the abdomen. Its meaning, however, is frequently extended to\ninclude double layers of peritoneum connecting various components of the\nabdominal cavity.\n","linknr":342,"url":"Mesenteric","recorded":1362484979,"links":44,"instances":["anatomy"],"pdf":[],"categories":["Digestive system","Abdomen"],"headings":["Mesentery (proper)","Development","Mesentery (general)","Pathology","Invertebrate anatomy","Additional images","Cookery","References","External links"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/19/Gray1038.png/300px-Gray1038.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8d/Gray1035.png/300px-Gray1035.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d8/Mesentery.jpg/250px-Mesentery.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/bf/Gray54.png/120px-Gray54.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/85/Gray985.png/120px-Gray985.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[["colon","anatomy"]],"members":["colon"],"related":["Anatomy","Peritoneum","Jejunum","Ileum","Abdomen","Jejunum","Ileum","Small_intestine","Nerve","Re